\cf0 D. Comments\
\
The wonderful insight of the designers of javadoc was the need to separate the task of parsing source code from that of generating documentation.  What I believe to be the wonderful insight of Ashkelon is the idea of persisting this parsed information in a manner that can later be used to aid developers and students of the Java programming language in their development and learning tasks, respectively.\
